# layouts.rules.mdc

### A. Purpose
Define the structural layout system for all Khwarizmi enterprise interfaces. Ensures consistent, accessible, and scalable screen architecture across all RealSoft products.

### B. Rules
- Every layout MUST use a 12-column grid system.
- Column gutter is 16px on desktop, 12px on tablet, 8px on mobile.
- All layouts MUST follow the three-zone structure: **Sidebar + Header (App Bar) + Main Content**.
- Sidebar is always on the **right side** (RTL-first).
- Header/App Bar is always fixed at the top.
- Content area must be scrollable independently from the sidebar and header.
- Breakpoints:
  - **Mobile**: < 600px — single column, hidden sidebar (drawer)
  - **Tablet**: 600px–1024px — 4-column grid, collapsible sidebar
  - **Desktop**: > 1024px — 12-column grid, persistent sidebar
- Page content must never span full 12 columns — use 10 or fewer for readability.
- Dashboard layouts MUST place KPI summary cards at the top of the content area.
- No floating elements that obscure primary content except modals and toasters.
- Z-index layers: Base (0) → Content (1) → Sticky elements (10) → Sidebar (20) → Modal backdrop (30) → Modal (40) → Toaster (50).
- Content regions must have clear visual separation using surface tokens, not borders alone.
- Minimum touch target for interactive areas: 44×44px.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Use the sidebar-header-content three-zone architecture on every screen.
- ✅ Design RTL layouts natively — sidebar on right, content flows right to left.
- ✅ Collapse sidebar to icon-only mode on tablet; hide entirely on mobile.
- ✅ Use 12-column grid with consistent gutters.
- ✅ Keep header persistent and visible at all times.
- ✅ Leave a minimum of 8px padding on all layout edges.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not create LTR-mirrored layouts and reverse them for Arabic.
- ❌ Do not use fixed pixel widths for content containers.
- ❌ Do not create fullscreen single-column layouts for desktop.
- ❌ Do not nest grid systems inside grid columns beyond two levels.
- ❌ Do not stack the sidebar below the main content on any viewport.
- ❌ Do not create one-off layouts not based on the 12-column grid.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating UI in Figma MCP or Cursor, always apply the three-zone layout template first.
- Auto-detect RTL context and apply right-side sidebar placement.
- When generating a dashboard screen, place KPI cards in the first content row, charts in the second, and tables below.
- When generating mobile views, always switch to a drawer-based sidebar and single-column grid.
- Do not deviate from layout zones without an explicit override instruction from the designer.

